💡The Ministry of Energy called on Ukrainians not to spread information about the consequences of enemy shelling 🗣️In view of the security situation in the country, the ministry asks:
• not to announce publicly (on television channels and radio broadcasts, in mass media, social networks) detailed information about the consequences of strikes;
• do not name specific objects of hits;
• not to provide details about specific objects and references to the area where air attack means were or were not hit;
• do not specify the number of hits and the place of hits;
• not to provide information in specific numbers and indicators — regarding blackouts, electricity shortages, etc. DMdetector.media The Ministry of Energy urged Ukrainians not to spread information about the consequences of enemy shelling.
